<subSubSection id="F7865BF72B8B579BD589C2A55D2F830C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="3F764430BDB06DB698D9E9BB225A4DF6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D84F59DCAAFFFBB18AA8737656C986B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Vigorous liana to 7 m, stems pubescent. Leaves petiolate, very large. 11-20 
<normalizedToken id="F55EF33729DF99587AAA936ADB633A8C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7-20 cm, ovate (rarely shallowly 3-lobed), acuminate to a fine point, cordate with rounded auricles, thinly to densely adpressed pubescent on both surfaces; petioles 5-15 cm, pubescent. Inflorescence of long-pedunculate, axillary, rather compact cymes; peduncles 8-30 cm, pubescent; bracteoles 10-11 mm, linear or filiform, finely acuminate, caducous; secondary peduncles 1-1.5(-10) cm; pedicels 3-14 mm, pubescent; sepals very unequal, somewhat variable in shape and size, outer sepals 12-17 
<normalizedToken id="D3795D8740C21D8028D804E915766D0E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5 mm, broadly lanceolate, acuminate, the tips usually recurved, pilose to glabrous, inner sepals 7-10 
<normalizedToken id="4A29CDDF912AA6252395FCA70CF259A9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, oblong, obtuse or acute, sometimes mucronate, pilose to merely ciliate, margin scarious; corolla 7-9 cm long, mauve, funnel-shaped with broad tube, in bud pubescent but glabrescent later, limb 5-6 cm diam; stigma biglobose. Capsules and seeds not seen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
